The paper deals with finding unbiased graph indices, which is a common problem in network science and can be applied to various fields. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the degree variance, which is a metric commonly used in network analysis, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a normalisation formula, which involves mathematical analysis, indicating that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible sub-categories.
